The paper deals with a fundamental problem in network design, which involves maintaining a low-cost subset of links in a given tree to ensure connectivity between terminal pairs. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), networking (cs.NI), algorithms (cs.AL), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely based on the relevance of the problem to each sub-category.
